Why&#039;d you blackmail your own employees?  That&#039;s not normal!

Shadow
私の店は、大手チェーンの直営店。優秀な私に経営は一任されております。
My shop is a directly managed store of a large chain.  Since I&#039;m highly competent, I&#039;m in charge.

Shadow
なので、店のお金をどう使おうと、他人様に文句を言われる筋合いはありません。
I don&#039;t need strangers complaining about how I use this shop&#039;s money.

Shadow
店の備品であるバイトの管理も私の自由なのです。
Part-time workers are the property of the shop.  Thus, they are mine to use as I will.

A
備品？あんた何様！？
Property!?  Who do you think you are!?

Shadow
そうか、お前ら、正義の面を被った強盗だな！迷惑な犯罪者は死んでもらう！！
I get it now.  You pretend to be heroes, but you&#039;re all just criminals.  I&#039;m gonna kill you!

M
いくぞっ！
Let&#039;s go!

#fight begins

Shadow
私の聖域を踏み荒らす無法者め！！王の裁きを受けよ！！
Outlaws who dare trespass in my sanctuary... Prepare to be royally obliterated by my hand!

#fight ends

Shadow
し、失礼いたしましたっ！…私など、店長に値しない人物でしょうか…？
I-I&#039;m sorry!  Am I really not worthy of being the store manager...?

&gt;その通りだ
気づけばいい
クビだ
That&#039;s right.
At least you realize it.
You&#039;re fired.

Shadow
ううッ、やはりそうでしたか…
*sob* I knew it...

Shadow
店員は備品ではなく、人財です。ようやく思い出しました！
I remember now... Employees aren&#039;t property... They&#039;re human beings.

Shadow
なのに私は、悪事のために利用していたなんて。
And yet, I took advantage of them.  I-I&#039;ve done bad things...

R
ブラックもいいとこだぜ。
Talk about a horrible workplace.

Shadow
なんと謝っていいやら…
I don&#039;t know how I can ever make up for this...

Y
他にも色々やってきたのだろう？洗いざらい話すんだな。
You&#039;ve done quite a bit more, haven&#039;t you?  It&#039;d be best if you just confess everything.

R
あ？中華スイーツ？
Huh?  Aren&#039;t those Chinese desserts or somethin&#039;?

Y
私腹を肥やしていた、…というわけか。
I see.  So he was lining his own pockets.

#entering next area

R
なぁ？ここってねエリアいくつあんだ？
Hey.  How many areas are on this floor, anyway?

A
一つ前は7エリアあったけど、その前は2エリアしか無かったよね？
The last floor had seven areas, but the one before that only had two, right?

Y
場所によってまちまちという事か…
I suppose it varies, depending upon the location...

R
んじゃあ、今が序盤か終盤かも分かんねェな…
Guess that means it ain&#039;t easy to tell how much of a floor we got left to cover, huh?

M
そういう事だ。最深部に着いてみなけりゃ、エリアの数は分からない。
That&#039;s right.  We won&#039;t know how many areas are on a floor until we make it to the end.

M
まぁ、シャドウの気配からすると、前より狭いって事は無さそうだがな…
But judging by the vibe I&#039;m getting from the Shadows... this floor isn&#039;t any smaller than the last.

#before the door into the next area

M
見ろ！あの壁だ！開くか調べてみようぜ！
Oh, look at that wall!  Let&#039;s check and see if it&#039;ll open up!

開く気配が無い…
It doesn&#039;t look like it&#039;s going to open...

Y
駄目なのか？
Hm?  Is it not opening?

M
どうやら、もっと大衆に受け入れてもらわなきゃ駄目みたいだな…
I guess we&#039;ll need to get more of the public to accept us...

R
それってぇ…まだ人気不足って事だよな…
So that means we&#039;re still not so popular, huh...?

A
あれ…ショックなの？
Oh... Is that a surprise?

Y
ああ…少しな。
Yes, perhaps somewhat...

R
お前かよっ！
She was askin&#039; me!

#before the next target (old man)

M
あの老人がオーノだな！これ以上、周囲に迷惑かける前に止めるぞ！
That old man must be Ono!  Let&#039;s stop him before he causes any more trouble for others!

Shadow
なんだ貴様らは！この王野平治に何か文句でもあるのか！？
Who the hell are you people!  Do you have some problem with me, Heiji Ono!

R
第一声で、いきなりソレかよ…
That&#039;s the first thing out of his mouth...

R
でも、吉祥寺で迷惑をかけているジーさんに間違いねぇみたいだな！
But it seems like this is the old guy who&#039;s making trouble in Kichijoji!

Shadow
いいねえ、嫌な顔が仮面越しでも分かるわい！
Nice, I can tell you&#039;re annoyed even with your masks on!

Shadow
それだけこの王野平治に興味があるってことだろ？ん？んんん？
That shows how interested you are in me, Heiji Ono, right? Riiight?

Y
…歪んでいるな。
...He&#039;s certainly disturbed.

Y
ジョーカー、さっさと片付けるぞ！
Let&#039;s end this, Joker!

Shadow
いいぞ、いいぞ、どんどん嫌がれ！もっとこの王野平治を見ろ！
Yes, yes, get mad!  Look at me, Heiji Ono!

#fight begins

Shadow
さあて、どんな嫌がらせをしてやろう…
Hmm, what kind of trouble should I cause next...

#fight ends

Shadow
…最初は、些細なことがきっかけだった。
...It started with something small.

Shadow
私がバカなことをすると、家族が心配してくれるんだ。
Whenever I&#039;d do something stupid, my family would worry about me.

Shadow
昔段はいないもののように扱う息子が、その時だけは…
My son usually treats me like I&#039;m worthless, but he would care for me in these times...

Shadow
それが心地良くて、いつの間にかよそ様にまで迷惑をかけて、かけて、かけ続けて…
It felt so good that I started seeking that kind of affection everywhere.  I ended up causing so much trouble...

Y
孤独がこじれた結果、か…
An unfortunate consequence of isolation...

Shadow
ううう…迷惑をかけ通しで、今更どのツラを下げて生きていけばいいのか…
*sniff* I&#039;ve caused so much trouble... How am I supposed to live like this?

&gt;まずは謝罪からだ
どのツラでも生きていけ
By apologizing.
In any way you can.

Shadow
謝罪？そんな今更な…
Apologize?  It&#039;s too late for that...

Shadow
いや、まずは始めることが肝要か。
No, the important thing is to start making up for it...

Y
…ご家族も、きっとそれを望んでますよ。
I&#039;m certain that&#039;s what your family wishes as well.

Y
それに、これからは他人に当たるよりも先にご当人に気持ちをぶつけるべきです。
And from now on, instead of taking it out on others, you should communicate your needs directly to your family.

Y
取り返しがつかなくなる前にきちんと「寂しい」、と。
Tell them that you&#039;re &quot;lonely&quot; before it&#039;s too late.

Shadow
ああ、そうするよ…
Yeah, I&#039;ll do that...

#6/13 begins, at train station

Akechi
こんな所で奇遇だね。
Fancy seeing you here.

Akechi
ああ、秀尽もこっち方面だっけ…
Oh, right.  I guess Shujin was in this direction too...

Akechi
にしても、君もこの時間だとはね。やっぱり僕たちは縁があるのかもね…
Still, I wouldn&#039;t have expected to run into you at this time.  Perhaps it really is fate...

Akechi
